        She wheels slowly toward the exit—alone, without Elder Twist, without the group's trust, without the role that defined her. Her flowers are still that exhausted pale, closed tight against everything.

        At the doorway she pauses.

        Florence says, "For what it's worth—the advice about the hostile plants was sound. De-escalation through clear boundaries—it's still the right approach." 

        Holloway says, "We'll consider it." 

